    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Georgetown College D. C</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>Feb 27<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1858</date>
            </p>
            <p><addressee>Rev. Dr Leeser</addressee>:</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Rev and Dear Sir:</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">Wishing some<lb/> books from you, I have written to my Father<lb/>
                    (<persName>Mr Isaac Levy</persName>.) and <sic>otained</sic> his
                    <sic>promission</sic><lb/> to write to you and get such books as I may<lb/> want
                and he will settle with your agent<lb/> in <placeName>Augusta</placeName>,
                    <persName>Mr Isaac Mayer</persName>, I have one<lb/> of your books which, I have
                been reading<lb/> and am well pleased with it (<persName>Dias</persName>
                Letters)<lb/> the books, I desire at present is first, a<lb/> good
                    <sic>chatechism</sic> of our faith, I saw<lb/> one some time since, which I
                liked very<lb/> much but unfortunately forgot the name<lb/> I know it was a large
                square flat paste<lb/>board back something like the Hebrew reader<lb/> then. I wish
                a Hebrew reader one wherein<lb/> I may learn the alphabet and first<lb/> rudiments
                of the language, then I wish<lb/> a book that explains the rites &amp;
                ceremonies</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>of our Holy Religion, and in which I<lb/> may find out when the holy days
                    <sic>ocur</sic>.<lb/> and if you have a small cheap Bible<lb/> you may send it,
                    <sic>thease</sic> book my dear<lb/> sir you may send either by express or<lb/>
                mail as you may think best and<lb/> sending the bill to <persName>Mr
                    Mayer</persName> it will<lb/> meet prompt payment, by attending<lb/> to this
                most Rev Sir you will confer<lb/> a Great favor. I remain yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Most Respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <persName role="author">Nathan E. Levy</persName>
            </p>
            <p>address</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Master <persName role="author">Nathan E. Levy</persName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Georgetown College</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <placeName>Georgetown D. C.</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>you may also enclose me a bill and your Catalogue<lb/> you will <sic>allso</sic> send
                me a couple of Good<lb/> instructive reading books, <persName role="author"
                    >NEL</persName></p>
        </body>
